<bibRefCitation author="Cheek, M" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B15" refString="Cheek, M, 2018. Stonesiaghoguei. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2018: e.T110074293A110074296. [Downloaded on 16 January 2019]" title="Stonesiaghoguei. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2018: e. T 110074293 A 110074296. [Downloaded on 16 January 2019]" year="2018">Cheek 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3417/2007080" author="Pfeifer, E" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="102 - 116" refId="B69" refString="Pfeifer, E, Grob, V, Thiv, M, Rutishauser, R, 2009. Stonesia ghoguei, peculiar morphology of a new Cameroonian species (Podostemaceae, Podostemoideae). Novon 19 (1): 102 - 116, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3417/2007080" title="Stonesia ghoguei, peculiar morphology of a new Cameroonian species (Podostemaceae, Podostemoideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3417/2007080" volume="19" year="2009">Pfeifer et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
assessed 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. ghoguei" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="ghoguei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">S. ghoguei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Vulnerable. The taxon is endemic to Cameroon and known from only one collecting locality, Tello Waterfalls. The extent of occurrence and area of occupancy are estimated at 4 km2 each. Their assessment is retained for now. IUCN List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Vulnerable VU D1 + 2</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
